The paper discusses computational complexity classes related to equilibria and fixed points, which are fundamental concepts in game theory, optimization, and other areas of computer science. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a highly likely sub-category. The paper specifically mentions Nash equilibria in games, which is a topic in cs.GT (Game Theory). The paper also mentions stable configurations of neural networks and stochastic models for evolution and language, which are topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses computational principles underlying different types of equilibria, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
